\f0\b\fs32 \cf0 Assignment:
\f1\b0\fs16 \

\fs32 Adapt any of the instruments provided in the code examples to produce single "cloud" of granular events when triggered by a GUI button, or by a keyboard event. The trigger will start a Routine that changes arguments in the instrument over time. It should have a discrete start and end, and be retriggerable, so that multiple starts produce new clouds that overlap. Play your instrument using your own samples and record a performance.\
note: this piece should be aroutine that has a beginnning and end - not manually contolled - you can make aroutine stop - Chris is going to send out  hint - look for it.   A simple way to achieve this is to include a stop button on the gui that could be triggered by the routine.
\fs16 \
